            "description": "Sanoma, one of the biggest Dutch magazine publishers was given the task by Disney to create a games hub for the Donald Duck IP and all its characters. They soon started a selection process to create a fresh, newly created team. At around 15 people, we were given this enormous task and to complete it within a year! My biggest role was building and redefining the city of Donald Duck, known as Duckburg. Scattered with all the other tasks, this took me around 6 month to complete. Besides the city I have also worked on a lot of the environments for the mini games, creating particle effects and overall art style creation and protection together with the team. \u2013 Created in 2014.\n\nDuckworld Smart Adventures is now live! Check it out at www.duckworld.com",
