            "description": "At ISOTX we worked on the free-to-play title March of War. A turn-based strategy game for PC and android/apple tablets. It is based on a World War 2 setting with a twist towards over engineering and diesel punk hardware.\n\nMy part / task:\nMy job description was modeling units and props. However I have also spent a lot of time fixing the art style where possible, giving all units a massive overhaul to make sure they fit in their faction style, recreating old or ugly assets, cleaning up source files, help resolving art bugs, managing documents like art workflows and outsourcing docs, helping the mapping team with all their art needs, advising other teams or projects where possible. In general, when it came to anything that had to do with art, I was involved.\n\nPortfolio images:\nhttp://www.robertberrier.com/portfolio/march-of-war-warzeppelin/\nhttp://www.robertberrier.com/portfolio/march-of-war-hammer/\nhttp://www.robertberrier.com/portfolio/march-of-war-gorillamole/\nhttp://www.robertberrier.com/portfolio/march-of-war-sickle/\nhttp://www.robertberrier.com/portfolio/march-of-war-warelephant/",
